"{\"uid\": \"theconversation.com-imane-khelif-the-algerian-boxer-who-overcame-an-ugly-gender-furore-to-win-olympic-gold-236175\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Professor of Sociology of Sport, Nord University  Anne Tj\\u00f8nndal is affiliated with The Norwegian Boxing Federation.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 115, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 87, \"end\": 114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_Boxing_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Norwegian Boxing Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_Boxing_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_Boxing_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"View all partners  https://doi.org/10.64628/AAJ.ka7eamckt  Share article  Print article  Imane Khelif'sgold medalat the 2024 Paris Olympics meant alsoovercomingafurorethat erupted around her and another boxer earlier in the games.Ugly issuesof gender identity, gender testing andtestosterone levelsonce againraised their head in elite women's sport.\", \"from\": 117, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif and Taiwanese boxer Lin Yu-ting failed aquestionable gender testadministered by the International Boxing Association (IBA) in 2023, but were declared fit for entry by the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 677, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 478, \"end\": 487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 3.731047931872962e-13, \"text\": \"Taiwanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 494, \"end\": 505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.324305242214079e-34, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 592, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both are female and identify as such, yet one of Khelif'sopponentssparked a public outcry that Khelif had an unfair advantage, spurring false claims she is transgender and with it a wave of online hate.\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We askedsport sociologistand former boxer Anne Tj\\u00f8nndal to explain what happened - and what else about women's boxing needs to be discussed.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Boxing was one of the last summer Olympic sports to include women athletes, with women's boxing being introduced to the Olympic programme for the London 2012 Games.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1169, \"end\": 1186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London 2012 Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In London,only threeof ten weight categories were included for women: 51kg (flyweight), 60kg (lightweight) and 75kg (middleweight).\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1191, \"end\": 1197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999998604548734, \"rank\": 1.3047954607840588e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the same games, ten weight categories were included for male boxers.\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The marginalisation of women's boxing continued throughout the Rio 2016 Games, maintaining three weight categories for women and ten weight categories for men.\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Things started to change after Rio, with the Tokyo 2020 games including five weight categories for women and eight categories for men.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1583, \"end\": 1586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.864379760289749e-12, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999937556069855, \"rank\": 6.244782960162463e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, men compete in seven weight categories and women in six.\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1690, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999982092049, \"rank\": 1.790683530344755e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the biggest controversies of women's boxing at the Olympics took place before London 2012, when AIBA (Association Internationale de Boxe Amateur - now the IBA) suggested it be mandatory for women boxers to compete in skirts at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 2002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1840, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1361374590212306e-19, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1917, \"end\": 1920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The suggestion was met withresistancefrom women boxers globally, and while the issue remained undecided as late asJanuary 2012, in the spring of 2012 it was finally announced that women boxers would be allowed to choose between competing in a skirt or in shorts.\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, the most pressing social issues for women's boxing at the Olympics relate to a lack of female representation in coaching and leadership, and a lack of research into the prevalence of harassment and sexual abuse of women in boxing.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Imane Khelif is a women's amateur boxer from Algeria.\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 2551, \"end\": 2558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999999263804993, \"rank\": 7.336646501700156e-08, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won a silver medal in the 2022 World Championship and a gold medal in the 2022 African Championship.\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2664, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In theTokyo 2020 Olympic Gamesshe reached the quarterfinals.\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 2725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heramateur recordstands at 53 fights (41 wins and 9 losses) at the time of writing.\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In recent news, Khelif has become a victim of widespread misinformation and unfounded allegations regarding her gender.\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She has been falsely accused of being transgender, despite living herentire lifeas a woman and having a long-standing career in women's boxing.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The controversy originated from the IBA's disqualification of Khelif from the 2023 World Championship.\", \"from\": 3075, \"to\": 3177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3111, \"end\": 3114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA cited her failure to meetgender eligibility tests, but has not specified the nature of these tests, sparking rumours that Khelif is transgender and biologically male.\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3182, \"end\": 3185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Misinformation, abuse and injustice: breaking down the Olympic boxing firestorm  The situation escalated after Khelif won her opening Olympic fight in 46 seconds against Italian Angela Carini.\", \"from\": 3354, \"to\": 3556, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3534, \"end\": 3541, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9902818647644174, \"rank\": 0.007705286059230524, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3542, \"end\": 3555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103660394, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This victory led to an increase in social media abuse directed at Khelif.\", \"from\": 3557, \"to\": 3630, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Carini's comment after the fight, claiming she had never beenpunched so hardbefore, further fuelled the allegations.\", \"from\": 3631, \"to\": 3747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3631, \"end\": 3637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999976267145907, \"rank\": 2.373291007216711e-06, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although Carini laterapologisedto Khelif for her behaviour, the controversy was exacerbated when the IBA announced that Carini would receive prize money equivalent to that of gold medallists.\", \"from\": 3748, \"to\": 3939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3757, \"end\": 3763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999976267145907, \"rank\": 2.373291007216711e-06, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}, {\"begin\": 3849, \"end\": 3852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 3868, \"end\": 3874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999976267145907, \"rank\": 2.373291007216711e-06, \"text\": \"Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Italian Boxing Federation has sincestated thatit will not accept this money.\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 4020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"score\": 0.9902818647644174, \"rank\": 0.007705286059230524, \"text\": \"Italian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3952, \"end\": 3958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.9999965244047789, \"rank\": 3.4755599764644513e-06, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost all sports competitions are organised in sex categories: a women's category and a men's category.\", \"from\": 4022, \"to\": 4126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The segregation of men and women's competitions is a founding principle of ensuring fairness in elite sports due to the athletic differences between men and women.\", \"from\": 4127, \"to\": 4290, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Caster Semenya: the legal and ethical issues that should concern us all  Gender testing has been used in elitesports competitions since the 1920s, and was initially introduced to ensure that men could not disguise themselves as women to participate in women's sports.\", \"from\": 4292, \"to\": 4569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking at the history of gender testing however, the \\\"sex-markers\\\" being tested have changed as medical knowledge has evolved over the decades.\", \"from\": 4570, \"to\": 4714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Several of the gender tests have since been provenmedically inaccurate and ethically flawed.\", \"from\": 4715, \"to\": 4807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Testosterone testing is commonly used in gender testing today.\", \"from\": 4809, \"to\": 4871, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4809, \"end\": 4821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4257484908862022e-49, \"text\": \"Testosterone\", \"types\": [\"Q11173\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Testosterone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women athletes who have \\\"too much\\\" testosterone are sometimes met with a demand for artificial regulation of their testosterone level.\", \"from\": 4872, \"to\": 5006, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if their bodies naturally produce more testosterone compared to other women athletes.\", \"from\": 5007, \"to\": 5097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The demand for artificial regulation of testosterone levels concerns two groups of athletes in particular: transwomen and women with intersex variations (women with difference in sex development or DSD).\", \"from\": 5098, \"to\": 5301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5296, \"end\": 5299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.999957165595527, \"rank\": 4.2836239437302384e-05, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is currently no indication to suggest that Khelif or Yu-ting are affected by DSD, as the IBA hassaidit's unable to share information about their gender testing for legal reasons.\", \"from\": 5302, \"to\": 5486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5385, \"end\": 5388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"score\": 0.999957165595527, \"rank\": 4.2836239437302384e-05, \"text\": \"DSD\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Signals_Directorate\"}, {\"begin\": 5397, \"end\": 5400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Boxing Association (IBA) was previously the governing body of amateur (Olympic) boxing.\", \"from\": 5488, \"to\": 5593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5492, \"end\": 5524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.324305242214079e-34, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 5526, \"end\": 5529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the International Olympic Committee (IOC)stripped it of its recognitiondue to persistent concerns over corruption and governance issues.\", \"from\": 5594, \"to\": 5734, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5602, \"end\": 5639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the Paris Olympics, a unit appointed by the IOC is organising the boxing competition.\", \"from\": 5735, \"to\": 5824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5783, \"end\": 5786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9220795317424776e-43, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 2028 Games, a new organisation named World Boxing is expected to replace the IBA as the governing body of Olympic boxing.\", \"from\": 5825, \"to\": 5954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5910, \"end\": 5913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:Olympics: Namibia's sprinters highlight a flawed testosterone testing system  The power struggles and tensions between the IBA and the IOC have raised questions about the IBA's motivations in addressing gender eligibility issues in Olympic boxing.\", \"from\": 5956, \"to\": 6213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5976, \"end\": 5983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\", \"score\": 0.9999999998731255, \"rank\": 1.2257209197861052e-10, \"text\": \"Namibia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Namibia\"}, {\"begin\": 6089, \"end\": 6092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 6101, \"end\": 6104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9220795317424776e-43, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6137, \"end\": 6140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many believe that the IBA is using the situation of Khelif as a strategy to undermine the IOC and garner global support.\", \"from\": 6214, \"to\": 6334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6236, \"end\": 6239, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9999992232236142, \"rank\": 7.767724147923035e-07, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 6304, \"end\": 6307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9220795317424776e-43, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Historically, women have been marginalised as athletes, coaches, referees, and leaders in boxing.\", \"from\": 6336, \"to\": 6433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In most countries, boxing continues to be a male dominated sport, which often contributes to limiting women's opportunities.\", \"from\": 6434, \"to\": 6558, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A pressing issue today is the lack of women's representation in coaching and leadership in women's boxing.\", \"from\": 6559, \"to\": 6665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Regarding gender eligibility in elite sports, women from the global south areover-representedin cases where the gender of female athletes is questioned.\", \"from\": 6667, \"to\": 6819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This article was updated to reflect Khelif's semifinals win at the Olympics  Copyright \\u00a9 2010-2025,The Conversation Media Group Ltd\", \"from\": 6821, \"to\": 6952, \"entities\": []}]}"